main event: A witness reported seeing a star-like object that moved slowly down, then up, and eventually disappeared.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for two minutes,The object was described as brilliant with a gold and red tinge,The observer noted that Venus was visible in the west at the time of the sighting,The object gradually sank below a line of trees,The preliminary analysis concluded that the object was probably a balloon, aircraft, or astronomical phenomenon.
witness description: housewife and elevator operator, member of local UFO spotters association
